members.description: The interconnect is degraded for an unspecified reason.

eventDetails.eventItemValue: Remove and re-insert the connection module. Verify that the connection module is installed in interconnect bay 1 or 4. If the problem persists, verify that the supported mezzanine card in server(s) is in correct slot matching the interconnect bay. If the problem persists, please contact your authorized support representative and provide them with a support dump.

members.description: The interconnect is currently configured for dual domain but communication with its partner interconnect has failed.

eventDetails.eventItemValue: Ensure that a SAS interconnect is inserted and powered on in both bays 1 and 4.  Perform a reset (soft) of the interconnect {"name":"CZJ9260730, interconnect 4","uri":"/rest/sas-interconnects/TWT012W03L"}.  If the problem persists,  perform a reset (hard) of the same interconnect {"name":"CZJ9260730, interconnect 4","uri":"/rest/sas-interconnects/TWT012W03L"}.

members.description: There is at least one link that is now functional on the network adapter at slot 3.

eventDetails.eventItemValue: This trap will be sent any time a physical adapter has had a function up at any point and transitions to having all of its functions down (including function types not in the cpqNic MIB) and then has one if its functions return to up. User Action: None Required.

members.description: The server has been powered on.

eventDetails.eventItemValue: The server has been powered on. This will be sent once a server power on transition has occurred.

members.description: Server reset detected.

eventDetails.eventItemValue: Server Reset Detected. The Remote Insight/ Integrated Lights-Out firmware has detected a server reset.

members.description: All links down in adapter in slot 3.

eventDetails.eventItemValue: Check the connection to the adapter and validate the connectivity from the server to any external device, including the cabling. If no problems are found, the adapter or other connectivity device may need replacement.

This trap will be sent any time a physical adapter has had a function up at any point and transitions to having all of its functions down (including function types not in the cpqNic MIB). User Action: Check the connection to the adapter and validate the connectivity from the server to any external device, including the cabling. If no problems are found, the adapter or other connectivity device may need replacement.

members.description: Connectivity is restored for adapter in slot 3, port 4.

eventDetails.eventItemValue: This trap will be sent any time connectivity is restored to a logical adapter. This occurs when the physical adapter in a single adapter configuration returns to the OK condition or at least one physical adapter in a logical adapter group returns to the OK condition. This can be caused by replacement of a faulty cable or re-attaching a cable that was unplugged. User Action: None required.
